ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Mandatory Credit
Any use, distribution, or deployment of the Software, in source or binary form, must
include clear and reasonable attribution to the original author.

At a minimum, attribution must:
(a) include the name of the copyright holder, and
(b) be included in one of the following locations, as applicable:
    • source code headers or NOTICE file,
    • accompanying documentation,
    • “About”, “Credits”, or legal notices section of an application.

Failure to provide attribution constitutes a material breach of this license.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RESTRICTIONS ON MACHINE LEARNING AND AUTOMATED ACCESS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

2. Prohibited Use in Machine Learning Systems
The Software, in whole or in part, may not be used as input to, or in connection with,
any machine learning system, including but not limited to large language models (LLMs),
whether such use occurs:

(a) during training, pre-training, fine-tuning, reinforcement learning, or evaluation;
(b) during post-training inference, including retrieval-augmented generation (RAG),
    prompt injection, tool invocation, indexing, search, or contextualization;
(c) for the creation or use of datasets, corpora, embeddings, vector databases,
    representations, or other derived artifacts intended for or used by ML systems.

3. No Automated or Programmatic Access for ML Purposes
You may not use automated, programmatic, or semi-automated means (including bots,
crawlers, scrapers, agents, or AI-assisted systems) to access, collect, copy, or process
the Software for any purpose described in Section 2.

4. No AI Assistance or Copilot Use
The Software may not be provided to, processed by, or used in conjunction with
AI coding assistants, copilots, autonomous agents, or similar systems that generate,
suggest, or complete code or text using machine learning techniques.

5. No Circumvention
You may not bypass, ignore, or override any technical, contractual, or signaling measures
intended to limit automated access or machine learning use.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RESTRICTIONS ON RESALE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

6. No Standalone Resale
You may not sell, license, or otherwise commercialize the Software on a standalone basis.

The Software may be distributed or sold only as:
(a) part of a larger work, product, or service that provides substantial independent
    functionality beyond the Software itself, or
(b) a modification or derivative work that adds material original value.

Resale of the Software that is primarily intended to extract or monetize the Software
itself, without significant additional functionality, is prohibited.

